I can remember. my father

716
01:25:12.800 --> 01:25:16.360
has left every morning and
he'd put a badge on his chest.

717
01:25:16.390 --> 01:25:19.880
and strapped a gun to his hip.

718
01:25:21.880 --> 01:25:24.870
And every day. for as
long as I can remember.

719
01:25:24.880 --> 01:25:27.880
I havenâ€™t known if he was
going to make it home.

720
01:25:36.280 --> 01:25:41.600
I got you. OK?

721
01:25:45.600 --> 01:25:49.140
I gotta stop him. though.

722
01:25:49.170 --> 01:25:52.680
I have to. cos I created him.

723
01:25:54.680 --> 01:25:57.360
What do you mean?

724
01:25:57.400 --> 01:26:01.320
I gave him an equation.

725
01:26:01.880 --> 01:26:05.800
I made all of this possible.

726
01:26:11.600 --> 01:26:15.060
Something my father's
been working on. you know?

727
01:26:15.090 --> 01:26:18.520
Secretly. now I realise
why he kept it a secret.

728
01:26:20.600 --> 01:26:25.080
Why this is my responsibility.

729
01:26:26.600 --> 01:26:30.400
I have to fix it.

730
01:26:39.080 --> 01:26:41.560
Let's get out of here.

731
01:26:41.600 --> 01:26:46.120
Let's get out of here.
just for a minute. can we?

732
01:26:46.150 --> 01:26:48.560
No. - Yeah.
- No. - Yes.

733
01:26:48.600 --> 01:26:53.600
No. - Yes. - If my parents
see me leaving I'm dead.

734
01:26:57.480 --> 01:27:01.720
Your parents are not
gonna see you leaving.

735
01:27:13.080 --> 01:27:17.160
<i>Peter Parker... Spiderman?</i>

736
01:27:17.200 --> 01:27:20.400
<i>I'm not the one who needs help!</i>

737
01:27:20.600 --> 01:27:24.080
<i>There will be no more
loneliness. no more outcasts!</i>

738
01:27:24.120 --> 01:27:30.600
<i>Species-wide distribution could enhance
humanity on an evolutionary scale.</i>

739
01:27:30.630 --> 01:27:34.200
<i>One has to adapt to survive.</i>

740
01:27:36.280 --> 01:27:39.740
That. changing like the
snake. I might be free.

741
01:27:39.770 --> 01:27:43.160
To cast off flesh
wherein I dwell confined!

742
01:27:43.200 --> 01:27:47.480
<i>Would you give it all up?
After all you know you can do?</i>

743
01:27:47.520 --> 01:27:51.600
<i>All the power you feel?</i>

744
01:27:53.800 --> 01:27:57.080
<i>I can save them!</i>

745
01:28:02.280 --> 01:28:07.320
<i>You are not gonna get in the
way of my plan. Peter Parker!</i>

746
01:28:33.000 --> 01:28:35.400
Go. go!

747
01:29:10.600 --> 01:29:13.800
Nowhere to hide. Peter.

748
01:29:30.000 --> 01:29:34.260
All these souls. lost and
alone. I can save them.

749
01:29:34.290 --> 01:29:38.520
I can sure them. there's
no need to stop me. Peter.

750
01:29:48.000 --> 01:29:51.080
You're not thinking straight doc.

751
01:29:53.480 --> 01:29:56.400
Stop this! This isn't you!

752
01:30:00.120 --> 01:30:02.400
Let's talk this out!

753
01:30:02.430 --> 01:30:04.520
Doc!

754
01:30:09.200 --> 01:30:11.320
Oh boy.

755
01:30:15.400 --> 01:30:17.720
Alright. so you don't want to talk?

756
01:30:17.750 --> 01:30:20.600
There you go.

757
01:30:23.000 --> 01:30:26.240
Don't... Make me...

758
01:30:26.270 --> 01:30:29.480
Have to... Hurt you!

759
01:31:07.680 --> 01:31:10.280
<i>Hey. - Where are you?
- I'm fine. I'm OK.</i>

760
01:31:10.320 --> 01:31:13.800
I'm down in the sewer. I'm tracking him.
I gotta stop him before anyone gets hurt.

761
01:31:13.830 --> 01:31:16.320
But we need an antidote.
do you know how to run a serum?

762
01:31:16.350 --> 01:31:18.880
<i>Yeah. I do it for
Connors all the time.</i>

763
01:31:19.120 --> 01:31:21.800
<i>I need you to go to Oscorp.
I need you to access</i>

764
01:31:21.830 --> 01:31:23.920
<i>the cross-species
file. it's a blue serum</i>

765
01:31:23.950 --> 01:31:28.880
<i>file 12389.
- OK. got it. On my way.</i>

766
01:32:00.320 --> 01:32:04.600
<i>I spent my life as a scientist. trying
to create a world without weakness.</i>

767
01:32:04.630 --> 01:32:06.680
<i>without outcasts.</i>

768
01:32:06.720 --> 01:32:11.120
<i>I sought to create a stronger human
being. but there's no such thing.</i>

769
01:32:11.150 --> 01:32:16.600
<i>Human beings are weak. pathetic.
feeble minded creatures.</i>

770
01:32:16.720 --> 01:32:21.120
<i>Why be human at all. when
we can be so much more?</i>

771
01:32:21.150 --> 01:32:25.070
<i>Faster. stronger. smarter.</i>

772
01:32:25.110 --> 01:32:29.000
<i>This is my gift to you.</i>

773
01:32:36.600 --> 01:32:38.800
Oscorp?

774
01:32:39.600 --> 01:32:42.320
Captain Stacy! - What?!
- We've got a confirmed sighting sir!

775
01:32:42.350 --> 01:32:44.480
The lizard is heading
toward Canal Street station.

776
01:32:44.520 --> 01:32:46.600
What about Spiderman?
- He was inside the high school.

777
01:32:46.630 --> 01:32:49.200
I want that Spiderman off the street!

778
01:34:36.320 --> 01:34:39.080
<i>The lizard creature has
released a biological agent!</i>

779
01:34:39.120 --> 01:34:45.120
<i>All efforts of stopping him have failed. he
is now proceeding north on 7th Avenue. over.</i>

780
01:34:48.480 --> 01:34:50.880
<i>Hey. where are you?
- I'm at Oscorp.</i>

781
01:34:50.920 --> 01:34:53.600
You have to get out of there right now. OK?
- The antidote is cooking.

782
01:34:53.630 --> 01:34:56.160
<i>No. no. no. Connors is on the way.</i>

783
01:34:56.200 --> 01:34:58.800
<i>He's coming to you right now.
he needs the disbursement device.</i>

784
01:34:58.830 --> 01:35:01.560
He's gonna infect the whole city...
- There's 8 minutes left.

785
01:35:01.600 --> 01:35:04.600
<i>You're gonna wait there for 8 minutes after
what I just told you? People are gonna die!</i>

786
01:35:04.630 --> 01:35:07.600
<i>You leave right now!
Listen. that is an order. OK?!</i>

787
01:35:07.630 --> 01:35:10.280
I'm gonna get everybody out.

788
01:35:10.320 --> 01:35:14.400
Gwen! You mother
hover. are you serious?!

789
01:35:29.920 --> 01:35:32.400
He's heading south!

790
01:35:08.800 --> 01:35:11.080
Stand down now or we will open fire!

791
01:35:11.120 --> 01:35:14.120
<i>You are surrounded.
there is no escape!</i>

792
01:36:17.600 --> 01:36:20.100
<i>Clear!</i>

793
01:36:20.130 --> 01:36:22.600
<i>Clear up!</i>

794
01:36:23.600 --> 01:36:26.400
<i>All clear here. sir!</i>

795
01:36:50.280 --> 01:36:52.760
Freeze!

796
01:36:52.800 --> 01:36:57.880
Down on the ground!
Put your hands behind your head! Now!

797
01:37:00.680 --> 01:37:02.920
Parker?

798
01:37:04.120 --> 01:37:08.920
It's headed to Oscorp. and your
daughter is there right now!

799
01:37:20.600 --> 01:37:23.600
You got to let me go.

800
01:37:36.120 --> 01:37:39.080
Hold your fire!

801
01:37:44.400 --> 01:37:46.720
Paul. if I didn't see
it I wouldn't believe it.

802
01:37:46.750 --> 01:37:48.970
I won't venture to say
exactly what it is that's

803
01:37:49.010 --> 01:37:51.160
crawling up the both
sides of the Oscorp Tower.

804
01:37:51.200 --> 01:37:55.320
but clearly it is not human
and it is very. very strong.

805
01:38:10.920 --> 01:38:13.720
<i>Time remaining: 1 minute.</i>

806
01:39:26.800 --> 01:39:30.120
<i>Antidote complete.</i>

807
01:39:41.400 --> 01:39:43.360
Oh man...

808
01:39:43.400 --> 01:39:46.280
<i>We are now getting the latest
details. this is just coming in.</i>

809
01:39:46.320 --> 01:39:50.600
<i>The New York police department has
called for a city wide evacuation.</i>

810
01:39:50.630 --> 01:39:53.360
<i>Everything south of 54th street.</i>

811
01:39:53.400 --> 01:39:58.280
<i>If you are south of 54th street you have
to move out of the area immediately.</i>

812
01:40:07.080 --> 01:40:09.960
<i>Spiderman appears to be
heading toward Oscorp.</i>

813
01:40:10.000 --> 01:40:14.280
<i>He looks injured and it is really
not clear if he's gonna make it.</i>

814
01:40:14.320 --> 01:40:17.080
This guy saved my boy on the bridge.

815
01:40:17.120 --> 01:40:20.480
They're clearing us out. something
bad is going down in mid town.

816
01:40:20.520 --> 01:40:23.600
Are you still friends with Mathews. that
crane operator down at the 6th avenue?

817
01:40:23.630 --> 01:40:25.560
Yeah.
- Get him on the phone for me.

818
01:40:25.600 --> 01:40:27.760
The cops are evacuating
everybody. who the hell cares?

819
01:40:27.790 --> 01:40:29.880
Get him on the phone for me!

820
01:40:47.880 --> 01:40:50.880
Hey Charlie. get me
Enriquez from 54th street!

821
01:40:50.920 --> 01:40:55.600
Angelo get your mug over here.
Walsky. you're getting some overtime!

822
01:40:56.600 --> 01:41:00.280
<i>All tower cranes on 6th. swing
your jib arms over the avenue.</i>

823
01:41:00.320 --> 01:41:05.080
<i>Boom angles at 90 degrees. Spiderman
needs those big boys high and lined up.</i>

824
01:41:05.120 --> 01:41:08.200
<i>Let's give him a
clear approach. over.</i>

825
01:43:39.600 --> 01:43:42.280
Dad. I have to get this to Spiderman.

826
01:43:42.320 --> 01:43:44.800
Get in the car. let's go.
- No. we can stop the lizard.

827
01:43:45.080 --> 01:43:48.360
You don't understand!
- I do.

828
01:43:48.400 --> 01:43:52.280
Your boyfriend is a man
of many masks. I get it.

829
01:43:52.320 --> 01:43:55.720
Give me this. get in the car.

830
01:43:58.920 --> 01:44:02.200
Please make sure he's OK.

831
01:44:13.880 --> 01:44:16.360
<i>Initializing GANALI device.</i>

832
01:44:16.400 --> 01:44:21.080
<i>Detonation in T minus 2 minutes.</i>

833
01:45:42.120 --> 01:45:46.520
Poor Peter Parker.

834
01:45:46.550 --> 01:45:50.920
No mother. no father.

835
01:45:51.200 --> 01:45:53.900
No uncle.

836
01:45:53.930 --> 01:45:56.560
All alone.

837
01:45:56.600 --> 01:45:59.480
He's not alone!

838
01:46:17.480 --> 01:46:22.120
<i>Detonation in T minus 45 seconds.</i>

839
01:46:28.920 --> 01:46:31.720
Hey. gift from Gwen!

840
01:46:33.000 --> 01:46:36.120
I got this Peter. go!

841
01:46:40.600 --> 01:46:44.120
<i>T minus 45 seconds.</i>

842
01:47:00.600 --> 01:47:05.080
<i>Detonation in T minus 10 seconds.</i>

843
01:47:05.120 --> 01:47:10.120
<i>9. 8. 7...</i>

844
01:47:10.800 --> 01:47:16.520
<i>6. 5. 4...</i>

845
01:47:16.920 --> 01:47:23.080
<i>3. 2. 1</i>

846
01:49:05.080 --> 01:49:07.480
The captain.

847
01:49:07.520 --> 01:49:09.880
Captain!

848
01:49:11.600 --> 01:49:16.120
The lizard...
- It's alright. we stopped him.

849
01:49:16.150 --> 01:49:19.600
Let's get you out of here.

850
01:49:21.880 --> 01:49:25.000
Look at me. stay with me.
Help is on the way. OK?

851
01:49:25.030 --> 01:49:31.080
You need to be gone.
when they get here. OK?

852
01:49:31.120 --> 01:49:35.880
I'm not going anywhere.
- I was wrong about you Peter.

853
01:49:36.120 --> 01:49:39.760
This city needs you.

854
01:49:39.800 --> 01:49:43.880
Here. you're gonna need this.

855
01:49:46.600 --> 01:49:50.200
You're gonna make enemies.

856
01:49:51.080 --> 01:49:54.560
People will get hurt.

857
01:49:54.600 --> 01:49:58.600
Sometimes people closest to you.

858
01:50:00.520 --> 01:50:04.400
So I want you to
promise me something. OK?

859
01:50:04.430 --> 01:50:09.800
Leave Gwen out of it.

860
01:50:10.600 --> 01:50:14.400
Promise me that.

861
01:50:18.000 --> 01:50:21.400
You promise me.

862
01:51:33.720 --> 01:51:37.080
<i>An eerie calm has set
in over New York city.</i>

863
01:51:37.120 --> 01:51:42.800
<i>Apparently some sort of aerosolized
antidote was launched from Oscorp Tower.</i>

864
01:51:42.830 --> 01:51:45.880
<i>which seems to have counter
acted the bio toxins.</i>

865
01:51:45.920 --> 01:51:48.360
<i>Residents of lower
Manhattan can rest peacefully.</i>

866
01:51:48.400 --> 01:51:51.200
<i>knowing that the alleged
mastermind of this terror plot.</i>

867
01:51:51.230 --> 01:51:55.320
<i>Dr. Curtis Connors is behind bars.</i>

868
01:52:33.400 --> 01:52:37.200
Sweetheart. it's OK.

869
01:52:37.880 --> 01:52:42.600
It's alright.

870
01:52:42.800 --> 01:52:45.760
Rough night.

871
01:52:45.800 --> 01:52:49.320
It's gonna be alright.

872
01:53:40.400 --> 01:53:43.400
Where have you been?

873
01:53:51.600 --> 01:53:55.320
My father died.

874
01:53:57.080 --> 01:54:00.680
There was a funeral.

875
01:54:00.720 --> 01:54:07.200
They shot rifles and made speeches.

876
01:54:10.000 --> 01:54:13.480
Two of my teachers showed up.

877
01:54:13.520 --> 01:54:16.920
Flash showed up.

878
01:54:19.720 --> 01:54:24.280
Everyone was there but you.

879
01:54:36.920 --> 01:54:40.120
I can't do it.

880
01:54:41.320 --> 01:54:45.080
I'm sorry. I can't...
- What are you saying?

881
01:54:45.120 --> 01:54:48.600
I can't see you any more.

882
01:54:48.920 --> 01:54:52.120
I can't.

883
01:55:15.600 --> 01:55:19.600
He made you promise. didn't he?

884
01:55:21.600 --> 01:55:24.400
To stay away from me.

885
01:55:24.430 --> 01:55:27.400
So I'd be safe.

886
01:55:52.120 --> 01:55:54.880
What a pretty girl.

887
01:55:54.920 --> 01:55:58.200
Yeah. that's what uncle Ben said.

888
01:55:58.230 --> 01:56:01.720
Did you ask her out?

889
01:56:03.600 --> 01:56:05.680
Why?

890
01:56:05.720 --> 01:56:10.280
I can't.
- Why?

891
01:56:12.280 --> 01:56:16.000
I'm just no good for her.

892
01:56:17.400 --> 01:56:22.000
Peter Parker. if there's
one thing you are. it's good.

893
01:56:22.030 --> 01:56:25.080
If anyone has a problem
with that can talk to me.

894
01:56:42.600 --> 01:56:46.920
<i>Peter. I know things have
been difficult lately.</i>

895
01:56:46.950 --> 01:56:50.080
<i>and I'm sorry about that.</i>

896
01:56:50.120 --> 01:56:52.920
<i>I think I know what you're feeling.</i>

897
01:56:52.950 --> 01:56:55.680
<i>Ever since you were a little boy.</i>

898
01:56:55.720 --> 01:57:00.920
<i>you've been living with
so many unresolved things.</i>

899
01:57:01.480 --> 01:57:04.760
<i>Well. take it from an old man.</i>

900
01:57:04.800 --> 01:57:07.800
<i>those things send us down the road.</i>

901
01:57:07.830 --> 01:57:10.280
<i>and make us who we are.</i>

902
01:57:10.320 --> 01:57:16.120
<i>And if anyone's destined
for greatness. it's you son.</i>

903
01:57:16.150 --> 01:57:22.600
<i>You owe the world your gifts. you just
have to figure out how to use them.</i>

904
01:57:22.630 --> 01:57:26.120
<i>And know that wherever they take you.</i>

905
01:57:26.150 --> 01:57:29.080
<i>we'll always be here.</i>

906
01:57:29.200 --> 01:57:32.360
<i>So come on home Peter.</i>

907
01:57:32.400 --> 01:57:37.000
<i>You're my hero and I love you.</i>

908
01:57:43.800 --> 01:57:47.200
Hello Parker.
- Hey. how's it going?

909
01:57:47.230 --> 01:57:50.550
You coming along man?

910
01:57:50.590 --> 01:57:53.880
That's a cool shirt.

911
01:57:53.920 --> 01:57:57.060
Yeah. dude's crazy.

912
01:57:57.090 --> 01:58:00.200
But chicks dig him.

913
01:58:13.320 --> 01:58:16.800
I had a professor once who liked to
tell his students that there were only

914
01:58:16.830 --> 01:58:20.280
ten different plots in all of fiction.

915
01:58:20.520 --> 01:58:25.080
Well I'm here to tell you he
was wrong. there is only one.

916
01:58:25.120 --> 01:58:27.360
Who am I?

917
01:58:27.400 --> 01:58:31.480
Mr. Parker. tardy again.

918
01:58:32.200 --> 01:58:34.360
Well. at least we can
always count on you.

919
01:58:34.400 --> 01:58:37.080
Sorry Miss Ritter. it won't
happen again. I promise.

920
01:58:37.120 --> 01:58:40.000
Don't make promises you
can't keep. Mr. Parker.

921
01:58:41.600 --> 01:58:44.360
But those are the best kind.

922
01:58:44.400 --> 01:58:48.600
OK class. open your books.
let's begin on page 1.

923
01:59:41.480 --> 01:59:48.480
<i>Subtitles by:
Sentinel</i>

924
02:00:28.680 --> 02:00:31.280
Hello doctor.

925
02:00:31.320 --> 02:00:34.160
Did you tell the boy?
- Tell him what?

926
02:00:34.200 --> 02:00:39.480
Did you tell the boy the
truth about his father?

927
02:00:39.520 --> 02:00:42.620
No.
- That's very good.

928
02:00:42.650 --> 02:00:46.060
We will let him be for now.

929
02:00:46.100 --> 02:00:49.480
You should leave him alone!

930
01:34:06.120 --> 01:34:12.120
<i>All efforts of stopping him have failed. he
is now proceeding north on 7th Avenue. over.</i>
